            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>Βασιλέος ἁγε<supplied reason="lost">μόνος</supplied>
                    <lb n="2"/>̒Ιέρωνος Ἱεροκλέος
                    <lb n="3"/>Συρακόσιοι θεοῖς πᾶσι
                 </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text of Kaibel (IG)</note></app>
                    <app loc="Line 1"><note>ἁγε[ομένου], Dittenberger</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <p>The Syracusans (dedicate this statue) of the king and hegemon Hieron, son of Hierokles, to all the gods</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>As John Ma, Statues and Cities (Oxford 2013) 20 n.27 notes, this is an anomalous instance of an honorific dedication where the honorand is in the genitive</p>
            </div>
